reviewText: OK  I like low budget movies and this was one to pass the day away.

Hard to find film.  Yet another take on the Bathory legend, perhaps a little more faithful than some adaptations.  Julie Delphy's and a recent Hungarian adaptation were closer to the account.  The streamed version of this called for digital remastering, as the print quality wasn't great.  But it was OK.  Just glad that it was available

The movie was good but the transfer was badly done as it was not clear even though it was through dvd r -recording.it should have been done better with a clear image and was disappointed with the quality of the transfer
